</i></p><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-14_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">In an era where information is abundant and accessible at the click of a button, maintaining the integrity and accuracy of news reporting is paramount. The Independent Press Standards Organisation (IPSO) plays a crucial role in upholding press standards and protecting the public from misinformation and unethical journalism. In this blog, Dr Richard Dune will delve into the importance of IPSO, key facts and statistics about its impact, definitions of relevant terms, and recommended best practices for adhering to press regulations. </span>
</p></div></div></div></div></div><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Previous" class="pf-slider-prev none hide"></button><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Next" class="pf-slider-next none hide"></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-03d9" data-category="Collection Suggestion" data-name="Tea" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-kYHfwS doYKjf pf-16_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hAcGzb cVhebe"><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-17_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-18_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-19_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-21_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">IPSO was established in September 2014 following the phone hacking scandal that exposed serious breaches of journalistic ethics. As an independent regulator, IPSO oversees over 1,500 print and 1,100 online titles across the UK. Since its inception, IPSO has handled over 40,000 complaints annually, demonstrating its critical role in maintaining journalistic standards and public trust in the media.






























</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-23_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-24_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-25_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-27_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-28_ pf-text-1"><strong>Independent Press Standards Organisation (IPSO) </strong>- An independent body to handle complaints and conduct investigations into editorial standards in the UK press.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-30_ pf-text-1"><strong>Press code of practice </strong>- A set of guidelines that newspapers and magazines agree to adhere to, ensuring accuracy, respect for privacy, and ethical reporting.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-32_ pf-text-1"><strong>Complainant </strong>- An individual or entity that complains with IPSO regarding a breach of the Press Code of Practice.
















</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-34_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-35_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-36_ pf-heading-1-h3">Importance of IPSO
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-38_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">IPSO's role is pivotal in ensuring that the press adheres to ethical standards, safeguarding the public from harm caused by inaccurate or sensationalist reporting. IPSO helps maintain accountability and transparency within the media industry by providing a mechanism for complaints and corrections.































</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-40_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-41_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-42_ pf-heading-1-h3">Best practices for compliance
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-44_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-45_ pf-text-1"><strong>Understanding the press code of practice</strong> - Media organisations must familiarise themselves with the Press Code of Practice, which outlines the standards expected in areas such as accuracy, privacy, and the reporting of vulnerable individuals.

</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-47_ pf-text-1"><strong>Training and education </strong>- Regular training sessions for journalists and editors on the Press Code of Practice and ethical journalism can help prevent breaches. Training programmes, like those offered by The Mandatory Training Group, ensure that staff are up-to-date with the latest regulations and ethical standards.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-49_ pf-text-1"><strong>Robust complaints handling</strong> - Establishing a clear and accessible complaints procedure within media organisations ensures that issues are promptly addressed and rectified. This helps maintain public trust and demonstrates a commitment to accountability.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-51_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regular audits and reviews </strong>- Conducting regular audits of published content to ensure compliance with the Press Code of Practice can help identify and address potential issues before they escalate.

















</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-53_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-54_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-55_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations for implementation
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-57_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">To effectively implement IPSO’s regulations and maintain high journalistic standards, organisations should integrate the following strategies:
































</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-59_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-60_ pf-text-1"><strong>Utilise compliance management software </strong>- Tools like ComplyPlus™ can streamline the management of compliance-related tasks, ensuring that all aspects of the Press Code of Practice are adhered to systematically.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-62_ pf-text-1"><strong>Engage in Continuous Professional Development (CPD) </strong>- Encouraging continuous learning through CPD courses helps journalists stay informed about ethical standards and regulatory changes.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-64_ pf-text-1"><strong>Foster a culture of accountability</strong> - Promoting an organisational culture that prioritises ethical journalism and accountability can significantly reduce the likelihood of breaches and enhance public trust.


















</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-66_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-67_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-68_ pf-heading-1-h3">The role of IPSO
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-70_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">IPSO guards press standards in the UK, providing a framework for addressing complaints and ensuring compliance with the Press Code of Practice. Its independence from government and media ownership ensures unbiased regulation, maintaining the integrity of the press.
































</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-72_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-73_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-74_ pf-heading-1-h3">Handling complaints
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-76_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">One of IPSO's primary functions is to handle complaints from the public. When a complaint is lodged, IPSO assesses whether there has been a Press Code of Practice breach. If a breach is found, IPSO can require the publication to issue corrections or apologies and, in severe cases, impose fines.

































</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-78_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-79_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-80_ pf-heading-1-h3">Investigations and sanctions
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-82_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">IPSO has the authority to launch investigations into serious Press Code of Practice breaches. These investigations can lead to significant sanctions, including public reprimands and financial penalties, thereby acting as a deterrent against unethical practices.


































